BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Indigenous Film Screening - Nechako: It Will Be a Big River Again
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260521T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260521T193000
UID:69c29efebf48d63c596c9a1e@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Nechako\nis a crucial documentary from Lyana Patrick that foll
 ows two Indigenous Nations fighting for our collective future. When the Ke
 nney Dam was built in the 1950s\, it diverted 70 percent of the Nechako Ri
 ver into an artificial reservoir\, severely impacting the lives of local S
 tellat’en and Saik’uz Nations. What followed were decades of resistanc
 e\, including legal actions against the Canadian federal and provincial go
 vernments and Rio Tinto Alcan\, a subsidiary of a global mining conglomera
 te.\nNechako\nfollows the people fighting today to restore a river and a w
 ay of life: Nations going up against industry\, community leaders advocati
 ng for their people\, Elders documenting their histories and community mem
 bers living off the land. An urgent call to action\, Patrick’s film asks
  what survival looks like when it serves everyone\, in a story 70 years in
  the making—a story of hope and resistance against all odds\, amidst lar
 ge-scale environmental destruction and despite the will of powerful instit
 utions.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this 
 form is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries
  Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be us
 ed for event and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Questions
  about how the library handles your information can be directed to Answerl
 ine staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toro
 nto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Albert Campbell\, Small Meeting Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c29efebf48d63c596c9a1e
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
